#####################################################################
# Installing DL4J
#####################################################################

reference: https://deeplearning4j.org/quickstart

1. Install JDK 1.7+ (64-bit version only)

Use the following command to confirm your Java installation:

java -version

2. Install Apache Maven 
(ref: https://maven.apache.org/install.html)
2.1 add a path to your JDK installation to the `JAVA_HOME` environment variable.
2.2 download Maven distribution archive from:

http://www-us.apache.org/dist/maven/maven-3/3.5.2/binaries/apache-maven-3.5.2-bin.zip

2.3 extract the archive to your preferred location:

unzip apache-maven-3.5.2-bin.zip

2.4 add the `bin` directory of the created directory `apache-maven-3.5.2` to the PATH environment variable

2.5 confirm your Maven installation with the following command:

mvn --version

3. Install IntelliJ IDEA

4. Install Git

#####################################################################
# Installing Keras with a TensorFlow backend for deep learning      
#####################################################################
(ref: http://inmachineswetrust.com/posts/deep-learning-setup/)

1. Install Python 3
Windows: https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
MacOS: https://www.python.org/downloads/mac-osx/

2. Install Anaconda
https://www.anaconda.com/download/

3. Adding Anaconda's "Scripts" to the PATH environment.

4. Setting up a virtual environment for our deep learning workspace

conda create --name deeplearning python=3.5 numpy scipy matplotlib scikit-learn

5. Activate the environment with the following command.

activate deeplearning

6. Install TensorFlow

pip install tensorflow

7. Install Keras

pip install keras

8. Test your installation by running

python mnist_mlp.py

